# RTL and Variant Rules (All Components)

- Build component variants from props (single component API), not separate per-language components.
- Do not create separate style sets/classes for LTR vs RTL unless explicitly requested.
- Components must be direction-safe by default.

## Variant Contract

- Use consistent variant names across components:
  - `size`: `small | medium | large`
  - `flush`: `true | false`
  - `expanded`: `true | false`
  - visual interaction state (as needed for preview/spec parity): `default | hover | pressed | focused`
- For first component (accordion), follow the same contract so the pattern scales to all next components.

## Logical Properties Only

- Do not use physical direction properties in styles:
  - avoid `left`, `right`, `margin-left`, `margin-right`, `padding-left`, `padding-right`
- Use logical properties/utilities instead:
  - CSS: `margin-inline-start/end`, `padding-inline-start/end`, `inset-inline-start/end`, `border-inline-start/end`
  - Tailwind logical utilities: `ms-*`, `me-*`, `ps-*`, `pe-*`, `inset-x-*` (when suitable), and logical border/radius utilities when available.

## Direction Handling

- Let document/container `dir` handle direction naturally; do not fork class lists per language direction.
- Keep component markup and class composition direction-agnostic.
